Step 1: Choosing a budget: Choosing a budget that caters to your organizations needs is an important decision so is understanding the available budgets to choose from and what comes recommended by the cloud service provider. The available budgets in AWS are;
-	Cost budget, which is the recommended one.
-	Usage budget
-	Savings plans budget
-	Reservation budget
See image: Step 1- Choose AWS Budget type.jpg

Step 2: Set your budget: When it comes to choosing your budget you need to specify the duration of time that you want to work with, will it be monthly? Or weekly?
You also need to include the period the specified budget will run from and when it will stop
Lastly, you need to specify the amount that you hope to spend with your budget in place. 


